# Cloudflare Pages cache rules.
# HTML must always revalidate so a new deploy's freshly-hashed JS/CSS is picked
# up immediately (no more "hard-refresh to see changes"). Vite's /assets/* files
# are content-hashed, so they're safe to cache forever (immutable).
#
# Order matters: /* is first, /assets/* is last — for assets both rules match and
# the later (immutable) one wins; HTML only matches /* (revalidate).

/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate

/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
